quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  13,38,We sent Messengers before you and gave them wives and children. Nor was any Messenger able to bring a Sign except by Allah´s permission. There is a prescribed limit to every term
  13,39,Allah erases whatever He wills or endorses it. The Master Copy of the Book is in His Hands
  13,40,"Whether We show you something of what We have promised them or We take you back to Us, your responsibility is transmission and the Reckoning is Ours"
  13,41,Do they not see how We come to the land eroding it at its extremities. Allah judges and there is no reversing His judgement. He is swift at reckoning
  13,42,"Those before them plotted but all plotting belongs to Allah. He knows what each self earns, and the kafir will soon know who has the Ultimate Abode"
  13,43,"Those who are kafir say, ´You are not a Messenger.´ Say: ´Allah is a sufficient witness between you and me, and anyone else who has knowledge of the Book.´"